title: Schools: Franklin field hockey battles Chelmsford to draw
text: Schools: Franklin field hockey battles Chelmsford to draw Senior Jill Sirignano scored early in the second half off a rebound to put the Franklin field hockey team (10-1-1) up a goal, but Chelmsford answered three minutes later and the non-league contest ended in a 1-1 tie. Comment   Writer Posted Oct. 11, 2015 at 8:58 PM Updated at 9:00 PM Posted Oct. 11, 2015 at 8:58 PM Updated at 9:00 PM Senior Jill Sirignano scored early in the second half off a rebound to put the Franklin field hockey team (10-1-1) up a goal, but Chelmsford answered three minutes later and the non-league contest ended in a 1-1 tie. Senior goaltender Samantha Jones made seven saves for Franklin, while senior Kenzi Pleshaw and sophomore Christina Quinn also played well. The Panthers are at Stoughton on Tuesday in a return to Hockomock League play.   Writer Posted Oct. 11, 2015 at 8:58 PM Updated at 9:00 PM
